Man was in car with Walter Scott when he was pulled over for a broken tail light in North Charleston . 
  Officer Michael Slager has been charged with murder after shooting the father-of-four in the back five times . 
  The man was in the car with Scott when Slager pulled over his Mercedes . 
  Slager was the subject of a complaint in September 2013 about excessive force . 
  The 33-year-old patrolman was allowed to stay on the force . 
  Mr Scott was shot dead by Officer Slager on Saturday in South Carolina . 
  Police report says the man was detained with Scott and put in a police car . 
 